<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Let me try to answer this...</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Ceyana">Ceyana</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 2:45 p.m. 18/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Let me try to answer this...<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1506" TARGET=_self>PvP Issues and Questions</A> (KingRThr3)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>

<BR>Make friends, that's all I can say. I've heard that they are going to change this, but when I don't know. I play a Dark Elf on the PvP server, and if i'm adventuring with them, they'll loot my corpse when I die and give me back the items/coin when I return, that way no one else can loot me. They're very honoreable, especially amoung friends. We police our own as well. If I see a dark elf looting a corpse that's not his, i'll confront the offender and kill him/her if they weren't grouped. Also, you arn't likely to die if you don't fight monsters that are too tough for you.
<P>They do need to work on the Guard AI and especially implement a faction system. This is the main imporvement that needs to be made on the PvP server. With a good faction system, there would be virtually no inter-racial pking, and that's what everyone really worries about I think.
<P>All in all, the PvP has been an INCREDIBLE experience. The system there adds so much that the other servers cannot. I went from the normal servers to the PvP, and I would NEVER go back! I'm definitely not a PK'er.
<P>- Ceyana
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
